elector_web_bevy/src/egui_theme.rs:5://! at compile time via `include_bytes!` so native builds work without any file IO.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/utils/setup_debug_scene.rs:1://! Implement `SetupDebugScenePlugin` that will spawn some flat ground, a camera and the sun.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/clouds.rs:1://! Standalone cloud skybox playground.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/clouds.rs:3://! Loads the flat debug scene (which brings in the procedural cloud sky) and\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/clouds.rs:4://! opens the cloud controls window, since there is no Debug menu here. See\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/clouds.rs:5://! [`demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy::plugins::cloud_sky`] for the details.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/turf_war.rs:1://! Turf War: a test arena where 4 AI factions fight each other and the player.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/turf_war.rs:3://! Drops ~5 peds per faction into a debug arena full of obstacles, sets them all at war,\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/turf_war.rs:4://! and lets them fight. A player-controlled pedestrian (faction Red) is spawned into the fray;\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/turf_war.rs:5://! the other three factions hunt it, its HP shows as green `HP: xx` in the bottom-right corner,\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/turf_war.rs:6://! and it respawns a few seconds after it dies. Dying peds (AI or player) play a death clip and\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/turf_war.rs:7://! then despawn. AI state transitions, shots, hits, and deaths are logged to the console.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/turf_war.rs:9://! Run: `cargo run --bin turf_war`\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/vfx_demo.rs:1://! Standalone VFX playground.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/vfx_demo.rs:3://! Loads the flat debug scene, and lets you spawn any visual effect at the clicked 3D point.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/vfx_demo.rs:4://! See [`demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy::plugins::visual_fx`] for the details.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/pedestrian_controller.rs:1://! Standalone demo harness for the [`PedestrianControllerPlugin`].\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/pedestrian_controller.rs:3://! Sets up a flat debug scene with some physics cubes, then auto-spawns a random controllable\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/pedestrian_controller.rs:4://! pedestrian once the manifest loads. All the controller logic lives in the reusable library\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/pedestrian_controller.rs:5://! module `plugins::pedestrians::pedestrian_controller_plugin` (also used by the main game).\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/pedestrian_controller.rs:7://! Controls: WASD move · Space jump · C crouch · Shift sprint · LMB jab · RMB(hold) aim ·\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/pedestrian_controller.rs:8://! LMB+RMB shoot · Esc back to freecam. In freecam, right-click to open the spawn popup.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/pedestrian_v2.rs:1://! Pedestrian V2 viewer — a thin driver around [`PedestriansPlugin`].\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/pedestrian_v2.rs:3://! This binary owns only viewer concerns: the scene (floor/camera/lights), spawning a grid of\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/pedestrian_v2.rs:4://! every pedestrian in the manifest, mouse picking + camera focus, and a single egui control\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/pedestrian_v2.rs:5://! window. All reusable pedestrian logic lives in `plugins::pedestrians`.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/audio_demo.rs:1://! Standalone 3D-audio playground.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/audio_demo.rs:3://! Loads the flat debug scene, fetches the sound-fx manifest and lets you fire any clip in 3D by\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/audio_demo.rs:4://! clicking the ground. See [`demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy::plugins::audio`] for the UI +\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/bin/audio_demo.rs:5://! playback details.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/cloud_sky/mod.rs:1://! Procedural sky plugin: blue-sky gradient, sun, day/night cycle, three\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/cloud_sky/mod.rs:2://! cloud layer types (cumulus / cirrus / storm), rain & snow overlay and\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/cloud_sky/mod.rs:3://! scrolling cloud shadows on the ground — all WebGL2-safe custom WGSL.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/debug_picker.rs:1://! Click-to-inspect debug window for free-camera mode.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/weapons/weapon_attach.rs:1://! Equipping a weapon: attaching/detaching the model on the character's right wrist, and computing\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/weapons/weapon_attach.rs:2://! its extents.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/weapons/weapon_manifest.rs:1://! Weapon manifest parsing via RPC.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/weapons/mod.rs:1://! Weapons: parse a manifest of gun/melee models and attach the chosen one to a character's right\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/weapons/mod.rs:2://! wrist. Combat animations elsewhere read [`EquippedWeapon`] to pick punch / sword / pistol clips.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/weapons/mod.rs:4://! Requires [`crate::plugins::pedestrians::PedestriansPlugin`] (it reuses that plugin's `TextAsset`\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/weapons/mod.rs:5://! loader for the manifest and its skeleton classification to find the right-wrist bone).\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrian_ai/spawn_ai.rs:1://! Spawning and adopting AI pedestrians.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrian_ai/perception.rs:1://! Line-of-sight perception for AI pedestrians.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrian_ai/movement_ai.rs:1://! AI movement and steering: translates AiState + perception into LocomotionInput.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrian_ai/combat.rs:1://! AI combat: directed gun fire, melee hits, punch, damage events, death.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrian_ai/debug_ui.rs:1://! AI debug gizmos and egui UI.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrian_ai/brain.rs:1://! AI brain: state machine that decides each ped's behavior.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrian_ai/anim_ai.rs:1://! AI animation driver: picks a base locomotion clip and triggers\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrian_ai/anim_ai.rs:2://! [`PedestrianAnimationControlEvent`] only when the clip changes.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrian_ai/mod.rs:1://! Pedestrian AI plugin: faction-based autonomous combatants.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrian_ai/mod.rs:3://! Spawned AI pedestrians receive a [`Faction`], [`Health`], and a behavior state machine\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrian_ai/mod.rs:4://! ([`AiState`]) driven by line-of-sight perception. Systems run un-gated (regardless of\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrian_ai/mod.rs:5://! [`GameControlState`]) so AI operates both in the main game and in headless test binaries.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/spawn_pedestrian.rs:1://! The pedestrian spawn path: turn a [`SpawnPedestrianEvent`] into a live, aligned,\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/spawn_pedestrian.rs:2://! classified pedestrian entity.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrian_ai/faction.rs:1://! Faction roster, war matrix, and health model for the pedestrian AI.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/skeleton.rs:1://! Bone classification for pedestrian skeletons (no rendering).\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/skeleton.rs:3://! Given the raw joint hierarchy of a rigged model, this labels each joint with a\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/skeleton.rs:4://! [`BoneLabel`] (head, spine, left arm, ...) using purely geometric heuristics.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/locomotion_consts.rs:1://! Shared locomotion speed caps, animation thresholds, and footstep playback tuning.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/arm_ik.rs:1://! Post-animation procedural arm IK for gun aiming.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/arm_ik.rs:3://! Runs after Bevy's animation evaluation and before transform propagation so shoulder/elbow\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/arm_ik.rs:4://! rotations override the animated pose while the lower body keeps playing locomotion clips.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/manifest.rs:1://! Manifest loading + animation-catalog bootstrap via RPC.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/spawn.rs:1://! Spawning, adopting, and despawning the controlled pedestrian, plus state transitions.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/draw_skel_debug.rs:1://! Debug gizmo rendering of pedestrian skeletons + the bone color mapping.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/controller.rs:1://! Kinematic character controller systems (ported/adapted from the avian3d\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/controller.rs:2://! `kinematic_character_3d` example).\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:1://! Playable kinematic pedestrian controller.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:3://! A pill-shaped (capsule) kinematic character controller (ported from the avian3d\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:4://! `kinematic_character_3d` example) moves on WASD, jumps on Space, crouches on `C` and sprints on\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:5://! `Shift`. The visible pedestrian model (spawned by [`crate::plugins::pedestrians`]) is parented\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:6://! *under* the controller as a purely visual child; the only physics body is the capsule. The\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:7://! controller yaws toward its movement direction so the single forward-facing locomotion clips work\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:8://! for movement in any direction.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:10://! Animations are driven directly on the model's [`AnimationPlayer`] so a locomotion clip and a\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:11://! combat clip can play *at the same time* (LMB jab, RMB-hold aim, LMB+RMB shoot layered on top of\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:12://! walking/crouching/sprinting/jumping).\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:14://! Integration with the main game runs through [`crate::plugins::states::GameControlState`]:\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:15://! right-clicking the map in freecam pops up a \"spawn pedestrian / spawn car\" choice; choosing the\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:16://! pedestrian enters [`GameControlState::ControllingPedestrian`], and Escape returns to freecam.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:18://! The plugin does not add `PhysicsPlugins`, `EguiPlugin`, or `PedestriansPlugin` — the host app is\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:19://! expected to provide those (the main game does via its physics/egui/states plugins).\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:21://! ## Entity / driver boundary\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:23://! A pedestrian *entity* is the shared capsule body + model; a *driver* decides what it should do\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:24://! each frame. Drivers are tagged with marker components so systems can filter without reading\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:25://! global resources:\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:27://! | Driver | Marker | Input source |\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:28://! |--------|--------|--------------|\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:29://! | Player | [`PlayerDriven`] | keyboard / mouse via [`character_input`] |\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:30://! | NPC AI | `AiPedestrian` | `ai_movement` brain |\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:31://! | Network | `NetworkDriven` | remote state interpolation |\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:32://! | Traffic | `TrafficPedestrian` (overlay on AI) | road-graph path follower |\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:34://! **Entity interface (shared):** drivers write to [`LocomotionInput`], [`MovementModifiers`],\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:35://! animation targets / control events, and weapon events (`FireGunEvent`, `ReloadGunEvent`,\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:36://! `PendingMeleeHit`, `EquipWeaponEvent`). Cars use the `Drive` event the same way.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:38://! **Entity behavior (shared):** [`CharacterLocomotionPlugin`] consumes locomotion input,\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:39://! `play_animations_system` plays clips, weapon observers handle firing, and car observers handle\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:40://! steering. Drivers never touch physics or animation playback directly (the player animation\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/mod.rs:41://! driver is a deliberate exception for combat-overlay blending).\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/animation.rs:1://! Animation graph + per-entity animation control for pedestrians.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/animation.rs:3://! A single shared [`AnimationGraph`] is built once (see `manifest.rs`) from the first\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/animation.rs:4://! pedestrian asset and reused for every spawned model (their bone names match). Consumers\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/animation.rs:5://! drive a specific pedestrian by triggering a [`PedestrianAnimationControlEvent`].\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/audio/mod.rs:1://! Audio engine plugin.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/audio/mod.rs:3://! Loads the sound-fx manifest (a plain-text list of `.ogg` / `.mp3` clip paths relative to the\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/audio/mod.rs:4://! manifest's own folder), preloads every clip as a [`bevy::audio::AudioSource`], and exposes them\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/audio/mod.rs:5://! through the [`SoundManifest`] resource. Once the manifest is parsed the\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/audio/mod.rs:6://! [`SoundManifestLoadFinished`](crate::plugins::states::SoundManifestLoadFinished) state flips to\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/audio/mod.rs:7://! `Finished`.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/interaction_ui.rs:1://! Freecam right-click \"spawn pedestrian / spawn car\" choice popup.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/camera.rs:1://! Third-person follow camera that trails behind the controlled character.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/camera.rs:3://! The camera sits over the right shoulder. Its orientation is controlled manually by **left-mouse\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/camera.rs:4://! drag** (yaw + pitch). Holding **right mouse** zooms in for aim (guns play the aim animation in\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/camera.rs:5://! `drive_character_animation`; unarmed/melee get the zoom only). Combat fires on the mouse-*down*\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/camera.rs:6://! edge, so a click jabs/shoots and the following drag rotates the camera.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/animation.rs:1://! Animation driver for the controlled pedestrian.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/animation.rs:3://! Unlike the shared `play_animations_system` (which hard-switches a single clip), this drives the\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/animation.rs:4://! model's [`AnimationPlayer`] directly so a **base locomotion clip** and a **combat overlay clip**\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/animation.rs:5://! can play at the same time:\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/animation.rs:6://! - base: idle / walk / jog / sprint / crouch / jump, chosen from controller state;\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/animation.rs:7://! - overlay: LMB jab (one-shot), RMB-hold aim (loop), LMB while RMB held = shoot (one-shot).\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/animation.rs:9://! The controlled model carries [`ManualAnimation`] so the shared system leaves its player alone.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/mod.rs:1://! Pedestrian engine plugin.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/mod.rs:3://! Loads a manifest of rigged pedestrian GLB models, spawns them on request, classifies their\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/mod.rs:4://! skeletons, and drives their animations via events. Reusable by any consumer (viewer binary or\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/mod.rs:5://! the main simulation).\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/mod.rs:7://! # API\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/mod.rs:8://! - On startup the plugin loads the manifest into [`PedestrianManifest`] (`urls`, `loaded`) and\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/mod.rs:9://!   builds the animation catalog in [`PedestrianAnimations`].\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/mod.rs:10://! - Trigger [`SpawnPedestrianEvent`] `{ url, position }` to spawn a pedestrian.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/mod.rs:11://! - Trigger [`PedestrianAnimationControlEvent`] `{ ped, animation, speed }` to drive one.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/mod.rs:12://! - Toggle [`SkeletonDebug`] `show` to draw the colored skeleton gizmos.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/locomotion.rs:1://! Shared character locomotion physics plugin.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/locomotion.rs:3://! Extracted from [`super::PedestrianControllerPlugin`] so both the player controller and the AI\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/locomotion.rs:4://! can share the same per-entity physics chain without double-registration. Both plugins guard-add\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/locomotion.rs:5://! this one:\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/locomotion.rs:6://! ```ignore\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/locomotion.rs:7://! if !app.is_plugin_added::<CharacterLocomotionPlugin>() {\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/locomotion.rs:8://!     app.add_plugins(CharacterLocomotionPlugin);\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/locomotion.rs:9://! }\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/pedestrians/pedestrian_controller_plugin/locomotion.rs:10://! ```\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/cars_driving/driving_plugin/car_disable.rs:1://! Disabling cars that have taken too much damage in the gang wars.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/map_plugin/bvh_minimap.rs:1://! Debug 3D minimap of the map-tile octree (Debug > 3D BVH Minimap).\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/map_plugin/bvh_minimap.rs:3://! Renders the cubic bounding boxes of every currently spawned map tile into a corner window,\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/map_plugin/bvh_minimap.rs:4://! seen from a virtual camera very high above the map so all boxes fit in frame. Tile boxes are\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/map_plugin/bvh_minimap.rs:5://! colored by their LOD state (active / pending reveal / splitting / merging / dropping), so the\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/map_plugin/bvh_minimap.rs:6://! split/merge churn — and what the BVH occluder culls — is visible while moving around the map.\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/map_plugin/bvh_minimap.rs:8://! Deliberately *not* a second `Camera3d`: instead the boxes are projected manually and painted\n/workspace/crack_demo/demo_resolution_selector_web_bevy/src/plugins/map_plugin/bvh_minimap.rs:9://! straight into the egui window.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1784667247757}]}
